The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 28: dlf has bagged a 25-acre property in Hyderabad for about Rs 450 crore. The realty firm plans to invest another Rs 750 crore to develop the property, which would either be an IT park or an IT special economic zone. We won the tender from the Andhra Pradesh Industrial Infrastructure Corporation for Rs 18.11 crore per acre, dlf executive director (southern region) Jaykrishna Subrahmanian said.

 New Delhi, Aug. 28: A meeting of the empowered group of ministers (EGoM) looking into the issue of natural gas pricing remained inconclusive today. The EGoM is likely to meet again on August 30, officials said.

 New Delhi, Aug. 28: Bharti Airtel is likely to be issued a showcause notice for putting up two towers within a distance of 10km of international border with Nepal in the Bihar circle. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 28: The government may give more concessions to the sugar industry which is bearing the brunt of over-production that has lead to a crash in retail prices.

 Mumbai, Aug. 28: Bombay Dyeing has got shareholders approval to raise about Rs 300 crore through issue of warrants, representing up to a five per cent stake in the company, on preferential basis to its promoter firm Bombay Burmah Trading Corporation Ltd.




